Description: Limestone altar in form of naos; marks of burning on top; incomplete.
Curator's comments: This small altar reproduces the shape of an Egyptian naos, a type well attested for Egyptian altars (Déonna 1934, 400-1; Soukiassian 1983, 331-2). Déonna, W. 1934, ‘Mobilier délien’, Bulletin de Correspondance Hellénique 58, 381–447. Soukiassian, G. 1983, ‘Les autels "à cornes" ou "à acrotères" en Égypte’, BIFAO 83, 317–33.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (ME.3) (Phase 3)
